data.title: What is the rank of Field Marshal in the US Army?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 5): Field Marshall does not exist within the ranks of the U.S. Army. The modern rank of General of the Army, which is denoted by five stars in a pentagon pattern, was created in 1944 as an equivalent rank to Field Marshall for American Army officers.
